ttps://ew.com/article/2015/09/10/flash-season-2-jay-zoom-wally-spoilers/ |title=The Flash season 2: New characters revealed by showrunner Andrew Kreisberg: Spoilers |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=2015-09-10 |website=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204221213/http://ew.com/article/2015/09/10/flash-season-2-jay-zoom-wally-spoilers/ |archive-date=2017-02-04 |access-date=2017-01-20|language=en-US}}</ref>。2016年初，加布里埃爾·史丹頓在第二季第10集〈潛在能量〉之後不再擔當節目統籌<ref name="Potential Energy">{{Cite episode |title=Potential Energy |series=The Flash |series-link=The Flash (2014 TV series) |network=The CW |date=2016-01-19 |season=2 |number=10|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="Stanton quit">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/dark-confessions-arrowverse/ |title=15 BTS Stories About The Arrowverse (That Threatened To End It For Good) |last=Czap |first=Travis |date=2018-03-06 |website=Comic Book Resources |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217054003/https://www.cbr.com/dark-confessions-arrowverse/ |archive-date=2018-12-17 |access-date=2018-12-14|language=en-US}}</ref>。{{link-en|亞倫·赫爾賓和托德·赫爾賓|Aaron and Todd Helbing}}擔當共同節目統籌<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.melty.com/the-flash-showrunner-promises-that-season-2-s-finale-will-be-packed-full-of-emotion-and-epicness-a4892.html |title=The Flash showrunner promises that Season 2's finale will be packed full of emotion and epicness |last=H. |first=Callum |date=2016-04-29 |website=Melty |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202000935/http://www.melty.com/the-flash-showrunner-promises-that-season-2-s-finale-will-be-packed-full-of-emotion-and-epicness-a4892.html |archive-date=2017-02-02 |access-date=2017-01-20|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/05/22/aaron-helbing-off-the-flash-in-season-4/ |title=Aaron Helbing Off the Flash in Season 4 |last=Burlingame |first=Russ |date=2017-05-22 |website=Comicbook.com |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004131615/https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/05/22/aaron-helbing-off-the-flash-in-season-4/ |archive-date=2018-10-04 |access-date=2018-12-14|language=en-US}}</ref>。

=== 選角 ===
第一季主要演員[[葛蘭特·格斯汀|葛蘭特·格斯汀]]、{{le|坎迪斯·巴頓|Candice Patton}}、[[丹妮爾·帕娜貝克|丹妮爾·帕娜貝克]]、{{le|卡洛斯·巴爾德斯 (演員)|Carlos Valdes (actor)|卡洛斯·巴爾德斯}}和{{le|傑西·L·馬丁|Jesse L. Martin}}確定回歸分別出演[[閃電俠_(貝瑞·艾倫)|貝瑞·艾倫／閃電俠]]、{{le|艾莉絲·威斯特|Iris West}}、[[凱特琳·史諾|凱特琳·史諾]]、{{le|震波 (漫畫)|Vibe (comics)|西斯科·拉蒙／震波}}和{{le|喬·威斯特 (綠箭宇宙)|Joe West (Arrowverse)|喬·威斯特}}<ref name="TeamFlashS2" />。[[湯姆·卡瓦納夫|湯姆·卡瓦納夫]]在第一季中飾演「[[逆閃電|逆閃電]]」[[艾爾伯德·斯旺|艾爾伯德·斯旺]]假扮的{{le|哈里森·威爾斯|Harrison Wells}}，在第二季中回歸出演2號地球中的哈里森·威爾斯<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.etonline.com/news/174383_the_flash_harrison_wells_earth_2_hes_a_dick_grant_gustin_tom_cavanagh |title='The Flash' Cast Dishes on Harrison Wells' Return: 'He's a Dick' (and No One's Thrilled!) |last=Aguilera |first=Leanne |date=2015-10-20 |website=Entertainment Tonight |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608073732/https://www.etonline.com/news/174383_the_flash_harrison_wells_earth_2_hes_a_dick_grant_gustin_tom_cavanagh |archive-date=2018-06-08 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref>。[[里克·考斯奈特|里克·考斯奈特]]在第一季中飾演{{le|艾迪·斯旺|Eddie Thawne}}，該角色在第一季最終集中死亡<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/19/flash-season-1-finale-eddie-death-rick-cosnett-spoilers |title=The Flash boss on finale's shocking departure |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=2015-05-19 |website=Entertainment Weekly |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818062820/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/19/flash-season-1-finale-eddie-death-rick-cosnett-spoilers |archive-date=2016-08-18 |access-date=2016-11-06|language=en-US}}</ref>。他在第二季首播集〈拯救中心城的人〉中客串回歸出演該角色<ref name="collider S02E1 review">{{Cite web |url=https://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-premiere-recap-the-man-who-saved-central-city/ |title='The Flash' Season 2 Premiere Recap: "The Man Who Saved Central City" |last=Trumbore |first=Dave |date=2015-10-06 |website=Collider |language=en-US |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514122552/http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-premiere-recap-the-man-who-saved-central-city/ |archive-date=2016-05-14 |access-date=2018-12-02}}</ref>，隨後又在第17集〈閃電俠回歸〉中客串出演<ref name="Cosnett" />。2015年8月，[[基南·隆斯戴爾|基南·隆斯戴爾]]確定出演主要角色[[華利·威斯特|華利·威斯特]]<ref name="WallyFlashS2" />，他是喬·威斯特的兒子<ref name="KreisbergOct2015">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/kreisberg-panabaker-on-latest-flash-developments-and-west-family-revelations |title=Kreisberg & Panabaker on latest "Flash" Developments and West family revelations |last=Mahadeo |first=Kevin |date=2015-10-27 |website=Comic Book Resources |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151029104448/http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/kreisberg-panabaker-on-latest-flash-developments-and-west-family-revelations |archive-date=2015-10-29 |access-date=2015-10-28|language=en-US}}</ref>。此外，葛蘭特·格斯汀、坎迪斯·巴頓、丹妮爾·帕娜貝克、卡洛斯·巴爾德斯和傑西·L·馬丁在第13集〈歡迎來到2號地球〉中各自出演2號地球中的相應角色<ref name="Earth-2 doppelgangers" />。湯姆·卡瓦納夫在〈拯救中心城的人〉和〈閃電俠回歸〉中出演「逆閃電」艾爾伯德·斯旺假扮的哈里森·威爾斯<ref name="collider S02E1 review" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2016/03/30/flash-tv-recap-no-matter-his-earth-this-show-revolves-best-around-tom-cavanagh/ |title='Flash' TV recap: No matter his Earth, this show revolves best around Tom Cavanagh |last=Betancourt |first=David |date=2016-03-30 |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |access-date=2018-12-17 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331150513/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2016/03/30/flash-tv-recap-no-matter-his-earth-this-show-revolves-best-around-tom-cavanagh/ |archive-date=2016-03-31|language=en-US}}</ref>。

Discussing the casting of Lonsdale, Kreisberg stated, "Just like when we met Grant [Gustin] for the first time, we instantly knew Keiynan embodied all the heart and courage of a hero. We are so excited to be bringing this much-beloved character onto the show."<ref name="WallyFlashS2" /> It was always intended for Wally to be the son of Joe and brother of Iris, which differs from the character's comic history, as the producers disliked second seasons of television series that would introduce cousins of characters that were never previously mentioned, feeling it was "weird".<ref name="KreisbergOct2015" /> Lonsdale originally auditioned for ''[[Legends_of_Tomorrow|Legends of Tomorrow]]'' to portray Jefferson "Jax" Jackson.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/07/flash-wally-west-lonsdale-martin |title=The Flash stars talk Wally West introduction |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=2015-12-07 |website=Entertainment Weekly |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209082111/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/07/flash-wally-west-lonsdale-martin |archive-date=2015-12-09 |access-date=2015-12-08|language=en-US}}</ref>

In July 2015, it was announced that [[Teddy_Sears|Teddy Sears]] would recur in the role of [[Jay_Garrick_(Arrowverse)|Jay Garrick]], the Flash of Earth-2.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-jay-garrick-teddy-sears-season-2-1201538467/ |title='The Flash' Casts DC Comics' Jay Garrick, Patty Spivot for Season 2, Teases New Villain at Comic-Con |date=2015-07-12 |work=Variety |access-date=2018-12-02 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616103319/https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-jay-garrick-teddy-sears-season-2-1201538467/ |archive-date=2018-06-16|language=en-US}}</ref> However, later in the season it was revealed that his character was actually [[Hunter_Zolomon_(Arrowverse)|Hunter Zolomon / Zoom]] posing as Jay.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.avclub.com/tvclub/zoom-reveals-all-and-barry-powerless-stop-him-flas-235518 |title=Zoom reveals all and Barry is powerless to stop him on The Flash |date=2016-04-19 |website=[[The_A.V._Club|The A.V. Club]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818065935/http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/zoom-reveals-all-and-barry-powerless-stop-him-flas-235518 |archive-date=2017-08-18 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref> Ryan Handley portrayed Zoom in costume prior to this revelation, while [[Tony_Todd|Tony Todd]] voiced Zoom.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2016/04/13/teddy-sears/ |title=Teddy Sears on What Makes The Flash Great, The Zoom Twist, and This Week's Big Episode |date=2016-04-16 |website=Comicbook.com |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612135847/http://comicbook.com/dc/2016/04/13/teddy-sears/ |archive-date=2018-06-12 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="ZoomVoice" />

=== Design ===
Maya Mani replaced [[Colleen_Atwood|Colleen Atwood]] as the costume designer for the second season and made slight changes to the Flash costume, such as changing the color of his chest emblem from red to white, being faithful to the Flash costume from the comics.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://fashionista.com/2015/09/fall-tv-costume-design-october |title=Costume secrets from the upcoming seasons of 'Reign,' 'The Good Wife' and more |date=2015-09-28 |website=Fashionista |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://archive.today/20181202065933/https://fashionista.com/2015/09/fall-tv-costume-design-october |archive-date=2018-12-02 |access-date=2015-09-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/03/a-visual-history-of-the-flash |title=A Visual History of The Flash |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |date=2017-10-03 |website=IGN |at=slide 28 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019205708/https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/03/a-visual-history-of-the-flash |archive-date=2018-10-19 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref> Gustin stated that, around the time of filming the season's ninth episode, "we stopped gluing the mask to my face and switched to a mask that just slipped on and off with a zipper".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvinsider.com/25346/outfitting-arrows-alter-egos-details-from-designer-maya-mani/ |title=Outfitting Arrow's Alter Egos: Details From Designer Maya Mani |last=Holbrook |first=Damian |date=2015-08-18 |website=TV Insider |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708105448/https://www.tvinsider.com/25346/outfitting-arrows-alter-egos-details-from-designer-maya-mani/ |archive-date=2017-07-08 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref> While Zoom's costume in the comics is a verbatim replica of Eobard Thawne's yellow-and-red [[Reverse-Flash|Reverse-Flash]] costume, the costume seen in the TV series is entirely in black.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://collider.com/the-flash-zoom-hunter-zolomon-comics/ |title='The Flash': Hunter Zolomon and Zoom's Comic Book Origins |last=Valentine |first=Evan |date=2016-03-01 |website=Collider |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217054003/http://collider.com/the-flash-zoom-hunter-zolomon-comics/ |archive-date=2018-12-17 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref> Kreisberg compared Zoom's appearance to that of the [[Marvel_Comics|Marvel Comics]] character [[Venom_(Marvel_Comics_character)|Venom]], saying, "The Zoom outfit is much more organic than the Reverse-Flash suit. In a way, it's hard to tell if it is a suit or alive… There's no skin showing, for all you know there's a robot underneath, or dark energy."<ref name="ZoomVenom">{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-zoom-tony-todd-season-2-villain-1201581891/ |title='The Flash' Casts Tony Todd as Voice of DC Villain Zoom in Season 2 (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Prudom |first=Laura |date=2015-08-31 |work=Variety |access-date=2018-12-02 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912040110/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-zoom-tony-todd-season-2-villain-1201581891/ |archive-date=2015-09-12|language=en-US}}</ref>

