=== Crossover with ''Supergirl'' ===
In February 2016, it was announced that Gustin would appear on the eighteenth episode of ''[[Supergirl_(TV_series)|Supergirl]]'', with Berlanti and Kreisberg, also ''Supergirl'' executive producers, thanking "the fans and journalists who have kept asking for this to happen. It is our pleasure and hope to create an episode worthy of everyone's enthusiasm and support."<ref name="GustinSupergirl">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/flash-supergirl-crossover-cbs-grant-gustin-melissa-benoist-1201695949/ |title='The Flash' and 'Supergirl' to Unite for Crossover Episode on CBS |last=Prudom |first=Laura |website=Variety |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204091618/https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/flash-supergirl-crossover-cbs-grant-gustin-melissa-benoist-1201695949/ |archive-date=2016-02-04 |access-date=2016-02-03|language=en-US}}</ref> While no plot details on the episodes were released at the time, Ross A. Lincoln of ''[[Deadline_Hollywood|Deadline Hollywood]]'' noted that "the in-universe reason" for the crossover was due to Barry's ability to travel to various dimensions, thus implying that ''Supergirl'' exists on an alternate Earth to the Arrowverse in a multiverse.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/02/supergirl-the-flash-crossover-official-in-march-1201695796/ |title=Crossover Confirmed: 'The Flash' To Meet 'Supergirl' In March Episode |last=Lincoln |first=Ross A. |date=2016-02-03 |website=Deadline Hollywood |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204034257/http://deadline.com/2016/02/supergirl-the-flash-crossover-official-in-march-1201695796/ |archive-date=2016-02-04 |access-date=2016-02-03|language=en-US}}</ref> "Welcome to Earth-2" confirmed this, showing an image of Benoist as Supergirl during a sequence where characters travel through that multiverse.<ref name="MultiverseSupergirl" /> The Earth that the series inhabits has been informally referred to as "Earth-CBS" by [[Marc_Guggenheim|Marc Guggenheim]], one of the creators of ''Arrow''.<ref name="GuggenheimOct2016">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/18/arrow-crossover-100-episode-spoilers |title=Arrow boss teases 100th episode, crossover catalyst |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=2016-10-18 |website=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021095428/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/18/arrow-crossover-100-episode-spoilers |archive-date=2016-10-21 |access-date=2016-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref>

In "[[Worlds_Finest|Worlds Finest]]", which aired on CBS on March 28, 2016, ''Supergirl'' is established as being in an alternate universe where the Flash helps Kara fight the Silver Banshee and Livewire in exchange for her help in returning home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/09/the-flash-and-supergirl-crossover-poster-and-plot-description-revealed |title=THE FLASH AND SUPERGIRL CROSSOVER POSTER AND PLOT DESCRIPTION REVEALED |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=2016-03-09 |website=[[IGN|IGN]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309193127/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/09/the-flash-and-supergirl-crossover-poster-and-plot-description-revealed |archive-date=2016-03-09 |access-date=2016-03-09|language=en-US}}</ref> The episode title was inspired by the ''[[World's_Finest_Comics|World's Finest Comics]]'' series, in which [[Superman|Superman]] would team up with various other DC superheroes, including the Flash. The events of this episode take place between two moments in the eighteenth episode of ''The Flash'' season two, "[[Versus_Zoom|Versus Zoom]]", which aired on April 19, 2016, in which Barry enters and exits a breach while wearing the tachyon device seen in this episode.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |title=Supergirl-Flash crossover: Everything you need to know, straight from set |date=2016-03-18 |website=Entertainment Weekly |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320153150/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |archive-date=2016-03-20 |access-date=2018-12-03|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-melissa-benoist-grant-gustin-andrew-kreisberg-cw-cbs-1201727447/ |title='Supergirl'-'Flash' Crossover: EP Andrew Kreisberg On How It Came Together |last=Dominic Patten |website=Deadline Hollywood |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520031339/http://deadline.com/2016/03/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-melissa-benoist-grant-gustin-andrew-kreisberg-cw-cbs-1201727447/ |archive-date=2016-05-20 |access-date=2018-12-02|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/Why-Didn-t-Flash-Talk-About-Supergirl-Crossover-All-132957.html |title=Why Didn't The Flash Talk About The Supergirl Crossover at All? |last=Holmes |first=Adam |date=2016-04-22 |website=Cinema Blend |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425045644/http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Why-Didn-t-Flash-Talk-About-Supergirl-Crossover-All-132957.html |archive-date=2016-04-25 |access-date=2016-04-25|language=en-US}}</ref> The crossover required "a lot more logistical trickery" than the usual Arrowverse crossovers due to Gustin filming ''The Flash'' in [[Vancouver|Vancouver]] alongside ''Arrow'' and ''Legends of Tomorrow'', while ''Supergirl'' is produced in [[Los_Angeles|Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvinsider.com/article/70539/the-flash-grant-gustin-to-guest-star-on-supergirl/ |title=''The Flash'' Heads to ''Supergirl'' |last=Holbrook |first=Damian |date=2016-02-03 |website=TV Insider |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205230502/http://www.tvinsider.com/article/70539/the-flash-grant-gustin-to-guest-star-on-supergirl/ |archive-date=2016-02-05 |access-date=2016-02-04|language=en-US}}</ref> The producers chose to use the Flash as the character to crossover, due to his ability to travel between various Earths, and because it was "a little more fun at first to bring the veteran from that show to the chemistry of a new show." Berlanti stated that "in a perfect world", the crossover would have featured both Gustin and Amell's Green Arrow, "but logistically that would have been a nightmare to try and do both shows. We had to facilitate one."<ref name="THRSupergirlCrossover">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-878275 |title=7 Things to Know About 'Supergirl's' Crossover With 'The Flash' |last=Bucksbaum |first=Sydney |date=2016-03-25 |website=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328183927/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-878275 |archive-date=2016-03-28 |access-date=2016-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref> Gustin was optimistic that the crossover in 2016 would allow another crossover the following year with the rest of the Arrowverse shows.<ref name="EWSupergirlCrossover">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |title=On the set: Everything you need to know about the Flash-Supergirl crossover |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=2016-03-18 |website=Entertainment Weekly |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320153150/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |archive-date=2016-03-20 |access-date=2016-03-20|language=en-US}}</ref>

The crossover episode received excellent reviews. Cliff Wheatley of IGN gave the episode an 8.6/10, stating "After the grim 'n' gritty ''[[Batman_v_Superman:_Dawn_of_Justice|Batman v Superman]]'', ''Supergirl''{{'s}} "Worlds Finest" offered a fun, upbeat palette cleanser and one of the series' strongest episodes to date. Instead of the usual "beatdown" introduction, Supergirl and the Flash went straight to being superfriends, which was refreshing. Not only did Barry Allen fit perfectly in Kara's world, but actors Grant Gustin and Melissa Benoist had fantastic chemistry together onscreen. While the city's turnaround on Supergirl's Red K incident was a little sudden, overall, "Worlds Finest" was delightful."<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/29/supergirl-worlds-finest-review |title="SUPERGIRL: "Worlds Finest" REVIEW" |date=2016-03-29 |website=[[IGN|IGN]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330072727/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/29/supergirl-worlds-finest-review |archive-date=2016-03-30 |access-date=2016-03-29|language=en-US}}</ref> Stacy Glanzman of TV Fanatic gave the episode a 5.0 out of 5 stars.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/03/supergirl-season-1-episode-18-review-worlds-finest/ |title=Supergirl Season 1 Episode 18 Review: Worlds Finest |date=2016-03-28 |website=TV Fanatic |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401232004/http://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/03/supergirl-season-1-episode-18-review-worlds-finest/ |archive-date=2016-04-01 |access-date=2016-03-28|language=en-US}}</ref>

